[{"text": "Come with me to the bottom of the world,", "start": 15.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Antarctica,", "start": 18.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the highest, driest, windiest,", "start": 20.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and yes, coldest region on Earth --", "start": 22.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "more arid than the Sahara", "start": 25.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and, in parts, colder than Mars.", "start": 27.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The ice of Antarctica glows", "start": 29.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with a light so dazzling,", "start": 31.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it blinds the unprotected eye.", "start": 33.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Early explorers rubbed cocaine in their eyes", "start": 35.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to kill the pain of it.", "start": 37.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The weight of the ice is such that the entire continent", "start": 39.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "sags below sea level, beneath its weight.", "start": 42.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yet, the ice of Antarctica", "start": 45.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a calendar of climate change.", "start": 47.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It records the annual rise and fall", "start": 49.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of greenhouse gases and temperatures", "start": 51.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "going back before the onset of the last ice ages.", "start": 53.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Nowhere on Earth", "start": 56.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "offers us such a perfect record.", "start": 58.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And here, scientists are drilling", "start": 61.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into the past of our planet", "start": 63.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to find clues to the future", "start": 65.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of climate change.", "start": 67.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This past January,", "start": 69.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I traveled to a place called WAIS Divide,", "start": 71.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about 600 miles from the South Pole.", "start": 73.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It is the best place on the planet, many say,", "start": 75.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to study the history of climate change.", "start": 78.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There, about 45 scientists from the University of Wisconsin,", "start": 80.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the Desert Research Institute in Nevada and others", "start": 83.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "have been working to answer a central question", "start": 86.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about global warming.", "start": 88.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What is the exact relationship", "start": 90.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between levels of greenhouse gases", "start": 92.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and planetary temperatures?", "start": 95.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's urgent work. We know that temperatures are rising.", "start": 97.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This past May was the warmest worldwide on record.", "start": 100.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And we know that levels of greenhouse gases are rising too.", "start": 103.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What we don't know", "start": 106.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the exact, precise, immediate", "start": 108.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "impact of these changes", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on natural climate patterns --", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "winds, ocean currents,", "start": 114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "precipitation rates, cloud formation,", "start": 116.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "things that bear on the health and well-being", "start": 119.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of billions of people.", "start": 121.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Their entire camp, every item of gear,", "start": 124.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was ferried 885 miles", "start": 127.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from McMurdo Station,", "start": 129.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the main U.S. supply base", "start": 131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on the coast of Antarctica.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "WAIS Divide itself though,", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a circle of tents in the snow.", "start": 137.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In blizzard winds, the crew sling ropes between the tents", "start": 140.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "so that people can feel their way safely", "start": 143.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to the nearest ice house", "start": 146.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to the nearest outhouse.", "start": 148.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It snows so heavily there,", "start": 150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the installation was almost immediately buried.", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Indeed, the researchers picked this site", "start": 154.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because ice and snow accumulates here", "start": 157.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "10 times faster than anywhere else in Antarctica.", "start": 159.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They have to dig themselves out every day.", "start": 162.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It makes for an exotic", "start": 165.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and chilly commute.", "start": 167.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 169.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But under the surface", "start": 171.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a hive of industrial activity", "start": 173.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "centered around an eight-million-dollar drill assembly.", "start": 176.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Periodically, this drill, like a biopsy needle,", "start": 179.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "plunges thousands of feet deep into the ice", "start": 182.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to extract a marrow of gases", "start": 185.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and isotopes for analysis.", "start": 187.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Ten times a day, they extract", "start": 190.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the 10-foot long cylinder of compressed ice crystals", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that contain the unsullied air and trace chemicals", "start": 194.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "laid down by snow,", "start": 197.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "season after season for thousands of years.", "start": 199.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's really a time machine.", "start": 204.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "At the peak of activity earlier this year,", "start": 206.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the researchers lowered the drill", "start": 209.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "an extra hundred feet deeper into the ice every day", "start": 212.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and another 365 years", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "deeper into the past.", "start": 217.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Periodically, they remove", "start": 220.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a cylinder of ice,", "start": 222.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like gamekeepers popping a spent shotgun shell", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from the barrel of a drill.", "start": 226.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They inspect it, they check it for cracks,", "start": 230.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for drill damage, for spalls, for chips.", "start": 232.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "More importantly,", "start": 236.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they prepare it for inspection and analysis", "start": 238.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by 27 independent laboratories", "start": 240.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the United States and Europe,", "start": 242.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who will examine it for 40 different trace chemicals", "start": 244.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "related to climate,", "start": 246.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "some in parts per quadrillion.", "start": 248.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yes, I said that with a Q, quadrillion.", "start": 251.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They cut the cylinders up into three-foot sections", "start": 254.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for easier handling and shipment", "start": 256.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "back to these labs,", "start": 258.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "some 8,000 miles from the drill site.", "start": 260.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Each cylinder", "start": 263.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a parfait of time.", "start": 265.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This ice formed as snow", "start": 268.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "15,800 years ago,", "start": 271.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "when our ancestors were daubing themselves with paint", "start": 274.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and considering the radical new technology", "start": 277.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the alphabet.", "start": 280.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Bathed in polarized light", "start": 283.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and cut in cross-section,", "start": 285.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this ancient ice reveals itself", "start": 287.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as a mosaic of colors,", "start": 289.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "each one showing how conditions at depth in the ice", "start": 291.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "have affected this material", "start": 294.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "at depths where pressures can reach", "start": 297.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a ton per square inch.", "start": 300.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Every year, it begins with a snowflake,", "start": 303.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and by digging into fresh snow,", "start": 306.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we can see how this process is ongoing today.", "start": 308.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This wall of undisturbed snow,", "start": 311.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "back-lit by sunlight,", "start": 313.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "shows the striations of winter and summer snow,", "start": 315.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "layer upon layer.", "start": 318.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Each storm scours the atmosphere,", "start": 322.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "washing out dust, soot,", "start": 325.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "trace chemicals,", "start": 328.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and depositing them on the snow pack", "start": 330.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "year after year,", "start": 333.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "millennia after millennia,", "start": 335.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "creating a kind of periodic table of elements", "start": 337.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that at this point", "start": 339.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is more than 11,000 feet thick.", "start": 341.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "From this, we can detect an extraordinary number of things.", "start": 344.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We can see the calcium", "start": 349.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from the world's deserts,", "start": 351.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "soot from distant wildfires,", "start": 353.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "methane as an indicator of the strength of a Pacific monsoon,", "start": 355.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "all wafted on winds from warmer latitudes", "start": 358.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to this remote and very cold place.", "start": 361.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Most importantly,", "start": 364.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "these cylinders and this snow", "start": 366.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "trap air.", "start": 368.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Each cylinder is about 10 percent ancient air,", "start": 370.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a pristine time capsule", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of greenhouse gases -- carbon dioxide,", "start": 375.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "methane, nitrous oxide --", "start": 377.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "all unchanged from the day that snow formed", "start": 379.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and first fell.", "start": 382.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And this is the object of their scrutiny.", "start": 384.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But don't we already know", "start": 387.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what we need to know about greenhouse gases?", "start": 389.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why do we need to study this anymore?", "start": 391.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Don't we already know how they affect temperatures?", "start": 393.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Don't we already know the consequences", "start": 395.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of a changing climate on our settled civilization?", "start": 398.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The truth is, we only know the outlines,", "start": 401.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and what we don't completely understand,", "start": 404.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we can't properly fix.", "start": 406.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Indeed, we run the risk of making things worse.", "start": 408.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Consider, the single most successful", "start": 411.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "international environmental effort of the 20th century,", "start": 414.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the Montreal Protocol,", "start": 417.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in which the nations of Earth banded together to protect the planet", "start": 419.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from the harmful effects of ozone-destroying chemicals", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "used at that time", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in air conditioners, refrigerators and other cooling devices.", "start": 427.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We banned those chemicals,", "start": 430.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and we replaced them, unknowingly,", "start": 433.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with other substances", "start": 435.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that, molecule per molecule,", "start": 437.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are a hundred times more potent", "start": 439.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as heat-trapping, greenhouse gases", "start": 441.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than carbon dioxide.", "start": 443.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This process requires", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "extraordinary precautions.", "start": 448.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The scientists must insure", "start": 451.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the ice is not contaminated.", "start": 453.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Moreover, in this 8,000-mile journey,", "start": 455.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they have to insure this ice doesn't melt.", "start": 457.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Imagine juggling a snowball across the tropics.", "start": 459.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They have to, in fact,", "start": 463.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "make sure this ice never gets warmer", "start": 465.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than about 20 degrees below zero,", "start": 467.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "otherwise, the key gases inside it will dissipate.", "start": 469.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So, in the coldest place on Earth,", "start": 472.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they work inside a refrigerator.", "start": 475.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "As they handle the ice, in fact,", "start": 478.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they keep an extra pair of gloves warming in an oven,", "start": 480.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so that, when their work gloves freeze", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and their fingers stiffen,", "start": 484.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they can don a fresh pair.", "start": 486.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They work against the clock and against the thermometer.", "start": 488.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So far, they've packed up", "start": 491.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about 4,500 feet of ice cores", "start": 493.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "for shipment back to the United States.", "start": 497.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This past season,", "start": 499.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they manhandled them across the ice", "start": 501.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to waiting aircraft.", "start": 503.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The 109th Air National Guard", "start": 505.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "flew the most recent shipment of ice", "start": 508.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "back to the coast of Antarctica,", "start": 510.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where it was boarded onto a freighter,", "start": 512.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "shipped across the tropics to California,", "start": 515.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "unloaded, put on a truck,", "start": 518.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "driven across the desert", "start": 520.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the National Ice Core Laboratory in Denver, Colorado,", "start": 522.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where, as we speak,", "start": 524.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "scientists are now slicing this material up", "start": 526.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for samples, for analysis,", "start": 528.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be distributed", "start": 530.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the laboratories around the country", "start": 532.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and in Europe.", "start": 534.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Antarctica was this planet's", "start": 537.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "last empty quarter --", "start": 540.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the blind spot", "start": 542.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in our expanding vision of the world.", "start": 544.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Early explorers", "start": 546.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "sailed off the edge of the map,", "start": 548.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and they found a place", "start": 550.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where the normal rules of time and temperature", "start": 552.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "seem suspended.", "start": 554.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Here, the ice seems a living presence.", "start": 558.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The wind that rubs against it", "start": 561.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "gives it voice.", "start": 563.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It is a voice of experience.", "start": 566.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It is a voice we should heed.", "start": 569.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 573.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 575.26, "duration": 4.0}]